<HEADLINE>
FT  23 AUG 94 / People: HP Bulmer
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
HP Bulmer, the cider maker, has appointed Alan Flockhart, 49, as its new
finance director, replacing Michael Ward, who recently took up the same role
with Lloyds Chemists.
Ward in turn replaced Richard Steele, now finance director at Storehouse.
Ward first joined the company in May 1989, leaving his post as finance
director of Bassett Foods.
Flockhart is no stranger to brewing; he is joining Bulmer from Wolverhampton
and Dudley Breweries, where he has been finance director since 1985. Before
that he was finance director of Scottish Brewers, a subsidiary of Scottish
and Newcastle.
The UK's largest cider producer - it makes nearly half of the 92m gallons
annually consumed - Bulmer recently adopted a new policy of recruiting 200
part-time tasters to help maintain quality.
