FT  22 AUG 94 / People (Names in the News): Cheng returns to family
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LOUISE LUCAS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Edward Cheng, executive director of Wharf Holdings, the Hong Kong
conglomerate controlled by the late Sir YK Pao, is to quit after seven years
with the company to take up a position in his family business, writes Louise
Lucas.
Cheng, who led the conglomerate's efforts to secure a publicly-declared
long-term debt-rating back in March - making Wharf the first Hong Kong
conglomerate to attain such a rating - was responsible for group finance and
corporate affairs, as well as the group's hotels business.
His finance duties will be picked up by Quinn Law, a non-executive director
of parent Wheelock who is currently in charge of corporate control and
treasury operations at Wharf.
