<HEADLINE>
FT  22 AUG 94 / This Week: Sport
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER BERLIN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Football
Wednesday, August 24, Glasgow, 8pm. Rangers v AEK Athens European Cup,
Qualifying Round, Second Leg.
Glasgow Rangers spent heavily on players again this summer. But their
expensive team was outplayed in the first leg in Athens and lost 2-0. They
must reach the second round, with its lucrative round-robin playoff system,
to profit fully on the investment. Worse, another early exit could
jeopardise Scotland's European Cup place and doom Rangers, even if they win
the league yet again, to a UEFA cup place next season.
Motor racing
Sunday, August 28, Formula 1, Belgian Grand Prix, Spa Francorchamps.
The Formula 1 season stages another roaring instalment of on-course tedium
and off-course melodrama. All the cockpit cameras, pit-lane cameras and
helicopter cameras, lovingly replaying every explosion and every crash,
cannot disguise the predictability of the racing: Berger following Hill
following Schumacher round one track after another. The only question that
remains is whether the authorities can suspend Schumacher before he amasses
an insurmountable championship lead.
</TEXT>
