<HEADLINE>
FT  22 AUG 94 / Business Travel: In the bag
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Britain lost out to Spain last week in what it prides itself on doing best -
making a cup of tea.
Spain's national airline Iberia won the 1994 In-Flight Best Cup of Tea Award
from Britain's National Tea Council, beating British Airways and British
Midland at making the national drink.
'We were absolutely delighted,' said an Iberia spokeswoman. To make the
award a team of tea tasters travelled 672,430 air miles on 239 flights with
30 different airlines. The defeated Britons were characteristically
tight-lipped.
