FT  22 AUG 94 / Business Travel: UK rail disruption
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Travellers to Britain today may be caught by the latest in a series of
strikes by rail signal staff.
The strike is part of what has turned into one of the most bitter industrial
disputes since the year long 1984-85 miners' strike. The dispute is over a
pay offer and plans for changes to working practices.
British Rail is running a significant minority of services despite the
strike.
