<HEADLINE>
FT  22 AUG 94 / Business Travel: Qantas facelift
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Australia's Qantas Airways has unveiled plans for a facelift to improve
services and make it more competitive with other leading Asian carriers
before the company's flotation next year.
Changes include new cabin interiors for the entire Qantas fleet of 120
aircraft, decorated with Australian designs and themes, as well as new staff
uniforms.
Qantas' managing director James Strong described the changes as the biggest
since the airline introduced the jumbo jet to its fleet more than 20 years
ago. Mr Strong said the changes would be introduced over the next year.
