<HEADLINE>
FT  22 AUG 94 / Business Travel: Philippine Airlines
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Striking ground staff at Philippine Airlines lifted their pickets and
returned to work last Friday in compliance with a Labour Department order,
union and management officials said.
Management will take back the strikers without retaliatory action. The
airline will also take back 40 union officers who led a June 16 strike,
until their cases have been decided by the Labour Department.
