FT  22 AUG 94 / World News in Brief: European Monetary System
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Against a backdrop of generalised D-Mark strength, bolstered by upgraded
growth forecasts and firm interest rates, the EMS grid was little changed.
The spread between strongest and weakest currency was maintained, with only
the Irish punt and French franc swopping places. Currencies, Page 27
The chart shows the member currencies of the exchange rate mechanism
measured against the weakest currency in the system. Most of the currencies
are permitted to fluctuate within 15 per cent of agreed central rates
against the other members of the mechanism.  The exceptions are the D-Mark
and the guilder which move in a 2.25 per cent band.
