<HEADLINE>
FT  20 AUG 94 / Property: Where to find your guest-house
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The West Country always has working guest-houses for sale. They range from
properties such as the thatched and listed grade II Newlands Cottage at
Newton Poppleford near Sidmouth at Pounds 140,000 (Fulfords, 0395-578126) to
seaside terraces at Pounds 79,950 in Paignton (Constables, 0803-529300) or
Weymouth (Palmer Snell, 0305-788727).
Constables in Exeter (0392-422122) and Millerson (0579-344401) both offer
Four Chimneys at Bratton Clovelly, on the north-west fringe of Dartmoor, for
Pounds 160,000; this was built in the 17th century as three cottages.
Others include the Victorian Withydown House at Stoke St Gregory, near
Taunton, for Pounds 220,000 (Stags, 0823-662822); Eastdown House near
Dartmouth, at Pounds 195,000; and Downhayes at Spreyton, near Crediton, at
Pounds 275,000 (both Jackson-Stops, 0392-214222).
Wales is also prime country for b&amp;b opportunities. Strutt &amp; Parker
(0244-320747) offers Carreg y Groes, overlooking the river Conwy in north
Wales, for Pounds 295,000, and Bodidris Hall at Llandegla, near Wrexham, for
Pounds 425,000 (with co-agent Christie, 061-833 3311).
The hall, a late 16th century manor listed grade II* amid nine acres, is now
a small country hotel. It is a receiver's sale.
In Norfolk, the imposing Victorian Holly Lodge at Heacham, near Hunstanton
(and Sandringham), has been a country house hotel. If it reverts to a family
house, there would still be enough bedrooms for b&amp;b guests. Price: Pounds
285,000 (Bedford, 0284-769999).
